criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        Pregnant women between the 36th and the 40th week of gestation undergoing spinal anesthesia
        for elective caesarian delivery.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. age < 18 yo;

          2. preeclampsia;

          3. eclampsia;

          4. atrial fibrillation and sinus tachycardia;

          5. cardiovascular diseases;

          6. neuromuscular disease;

          7. emergent or urgent cesarean delivery;

          8. coagulopathies;

          9. contraindications to spinal anesthesia.
